item.description:
How to avoid Tiller Helm 2.x uses a server side component called tiller. Typically Tiller is installed in a global namespace; or you can install a Tiller in each namespace and configure your helm CLI to talk to the right tiller in the right namespace.
However Tiller has a number of issues&hellip;
The problem with Tiller  complicates RBAC since its not using the RBAC of the user or pod running the helm commands to read/write kubernetes resources - helm is talking to the remote tiller pod to do the work.
